{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "project-notification-update-workflow-collection",
    "name": "Project Notification Update Workflow API",
    "description": "Workflow-based update and lifecycle actions for project notifications.\n\nFlow:\n1. POST /projects/notifications/{id}/request-update → submit new data + files (creates a Process).\n2. Approver sees the pending Process step in their inbox.\n3. POST /projects/notifications/{id}/approve → approves the current step.\n4. On final approval the ProjectNotification row is updated with the submitted data and files are moved to the attachments collection.\n5. POST /projects/notifications/{id}/end → close the notification (endProjectNotificationTask). Requires latitude/longitude; accepts up to 10 closing screenshot files (files[], jpg/jpeg/png/webp, max 5MB each). If InsideTaskLocation is active on the form's procedure setting, the employee must be within the configured radius of the task location.\n\nMobile inbox logic:\n- GET /projects/notifications/my-inbox returns pending_processes with a stable mobile_inbox_action_key.\n- confirm_receive → open the confirm-receive screen (POST /projects/notifications/{id}/confirm-receive).\n- accept_reject → open the accept/reject screen (POST /projects/notifications/{id}/approve or /reject).\n- GET /projects/notifications/{id}/available-actions also returns mobile_inbox_action_key for each action.\n\nForms with optional InsideTaskLocation precondition:\n- request-site-status-update (uses current_latitude/current_longitude when supplied)\n- request-fine (uses current_latitude/current_longitude when supplied)\n- confirm-location (uses latitude/longitude)\n- end (uses latitude/longitude)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "url",
      "value": "http://localhost/api/v1",
      "type": "string"
    },
